  "title": "He Stole a Kayak and Used a Snow Shovel as a Paddle",
  "script": "Drunk. Wrong paddle. Stolen kayak! In Behchoko, Northwest Territories, Canada, a 63-year-old man stole a kayak, grabbed a snow shovel to use as a paddle, and launched himself onto Marion Lake — drunk. He paddled around for a while, then capsized. He couldn't swim to shore. RCMP officers had to fish him out and arrest him on the spot. He was charged with impaired operation of a vessel and refusing a breathalyzer. Now think about the sequence of decisions here: decide to go kayaking drunk, realize you have no paddle, grab a snow shovel instead, steal a neighbor's kayak, capsize anyway, and then refuse to blow. Each one of those was a choice. The snow shovel — that one took real creativity. Was the shovel the first bad idea here, or the fourth?",
